messages.text:
Essay
This letter is intended to describe in detail the reason for the long-term departure to Germany, the expectations associated with the planned stay in Germany, and the expected professional and personal benefits, as well as plans for the future while studying at the Deggendorf Institute of Technology.
The main reason for staying in Germany for this period is related to studying in the Artificial Intelligence course at the Deggendorf Institute of Technology. The Deggendorf Institute of Technology trains specialists in German and English. For me, this is a good chance to get a high-level education in English. I received an invitation to study at this university on August 4, 2022.
I'm going to study in Germany to further develop my country Kazakhstan in the IT field. I think that my course, which teaches not only programming but also business management, will help me become a highly qualified and in-demand specialist.
While studying at the Deggendorf Institute of Technology, I'm going to learn German to have an idea of German culture, interact with the locals and improve my networking skills. I am keen to find new diversified friends from different countries and I am open to interacting to learn about new cultures as well as share my Kazakh history. Moreover, I plan to do an internship at German IT company. The university provides many opportunities for students, so I also plan to engage in musical activity as a hobby.
 There are more than 6 thousand students at the Deggendorf Institute of Technology. While studying at this university, I will be able to develop not only hard skills such as programming and business management, but also soft skills such as teamwork and communication skills. International students are also present at this institute, so I will be able to broaden my horizons and learn more about their culture and history.

Date, place_______

Signature________

In Germany, the use of racist language, including the use of the N-word, can be reported to various authorities and organizations. Here are steps you can take to report such incidents:

1. Immediate Safety Concerns
If the situation involves immediate danger or threats, contact the police by dialing 110.

2. Police Report
For non-emergency situations, you can file a report with the local police. You can do this by visiting the nearest police station or by filing a report online in some states.

3. Anti-Discrimination Agencies
Germany has several agencies dedicated to fighting discrimination and supporting victims of racism. You can contact:

Federal Anti-Discrimination Agency (Antidiskriminierungsstelle des Bundes): They provide advice and support to victims of discrimination.
Website:

4. Civil Society Organizations
Several organizations work against racism and discrimination in Germany. These organizations can offer support and advice, and in some cases, help you report incidents:

Amadeu Antonio Foundation (Amadeu Antonio Stiftung): Provides support to victims of racism and right-wing violence.
Website:

Network Against Racism (Netzwerk gegen Rassismus): Offers resources and support for combating racism.
Website:

Germany‚Äôs Federal Association of Victim Support (Weisser Ring): Offers help and support to victims of crime.
Website:

5. Reporting Platforms
There are online platforms where you can report incidents of racism and hate speech:

HateAid: Provides legal advice and support for victims of online hate speech.
Website:

Respect! No Place for Racism (Respekt! Kein Platz f√ºr Rassismus): Allows reporting of racism and offers resources for support.
Website:

6. Legal Advice
If you need legal advice or want to pursue legal action, consider contacting a lawyer who specializes in discrimination law. There are also organizations that offer free or low-cost legal advice to victims of discrimination.

Steps to Take:
Document the Incident: Write down all details about the incident including date, time, location, and any witnesses.
Gather Evidence: If possible, gather evidence such as photos, videos, or messages that contain the abusive language.
Contact the Authorities/Organizations: Use the information provided above to contact the appropriate authority or organization.
Seek Support: Reach out to support groups or counseling services if you need emotional or psychological support.
By taking these steps, you can help address and combat racist language and behavior in Germany.
